This paper is about a new architecture for medical image segmentation, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the use of deep supervision, which is a technique commonly used in deep learning (cs.LG). The architecture is designed to reduce the semantic gap between the encoder and decoder sub-networks, which involves improving the understanding of the semantic meaning of the images, which is a topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also evaluates the architecture on multiple medical image segmentation tasks, which involves analyzing and processing images, a topic in multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the paper discusses the use of an optimizer to improve learning, which is a topic in neural networks (cs.NE).
